This season, the Phoenix Suns have become one of the most unstoppable teams in the NBA after beating the Western Conference leader Golden State Warriors to achieve a 17-game winning streak, matching franchise record. Considering they are hosting Eastern Conference bottom ranking Detroit Pistons on Thursday, setting a new record seems to be only a matter of time. The Suns have made the NBA Finals three times so far but lost every series in 1976, 1993 and 2021. Can they make a difference this time? Host: Li Xiang Guest: Matthew Watson Cover designer: Feng Yuan Chief editor: Chen Ran Supervisor: Zhang Shilei